Documents the pipeline that actually exists in this repository as of
53 certified templates across 9 chapters — not the original aspirational
Math Teacher OS vision docs (docs/architecture/math-teacher-os-*),
which pre-date this pipeline and describe a broader, not-yet-built
multi-course platform. This new document is deliberately narrow and
concrete: what exists, where it lives, how to extend it safely.

Covers:
- The six-engine certification chain (Resolver -> Variable Generator
  -> Solver -> Distractor Engine -> Prompt Renderer -> Figure
  Renderer) plus the two composition layers built on top (Question
  Factory, Quiz Composer).
- A file map distinguishing this certified pipeline from the
  pre-existing, unconnected legacy architecture
  (questionFactory.js / geometryQuestionEngine.js — different data
  model, do not confuse the two).
- The 53 templates broken down by chapter, with an explicit warning
  not to trust the table as a source of truth — call
  geometryVariableGenerator.getSupportedTemplateIds() instead, since
  the list can only drift out of sync with the actual registry if
  someone edits the table by hand and forgets the code.
- The design decisions that matter before extending the system:
  exact (never rounded) answers, distractors grounded in named
  student errors, and — the single most important lesson from this
  project — why a single seed is never enough to certify a
  distractor function, illustrated with the four real, confirmed
  bugs found this way during development (vertical angle pair
  missing fields, similar-polygon-scale-factor fallback failure,
  circle-equation's two separate collision bugs including the -0===0
  origin case, and midpoint's four-simultaneous-collision origin
  case found by the Quiz Composer months after the template's own
  original stress tests had passed).
- The exact two-commit recipe used nine times now to add a new
  chapter's worth of templates, so it doesn't have to be
  re-discovered from commit archaeology next time.
- Known gaps: Chapter 2's proof-writing sections (deliberately out of
  scope), figures existing for only 12 of 53 templates, the
  unconnected legacy Quality Gate, and the still-undeleted dead
  geometryQuestionEngine.js.
- The verification philosophy applied to every commit in this
  pipeline's history (build -> stress-test locally -> full
  regression -> commit -> clone fresh and re-verify against the real
  pushed repository), stated explicitly since it's easy to skip
  under time pressure and is the reason this pipeline has zero
  known distractor collisions in production despite having found and
  fixed four of them during development.

Verified every file path and the 53-template count mentioned in this
document against the actual repository state before committing —
docs describing paths or numbers that don't match reality are worse
than no docs at all.
